    ns1:inpersonHours "64 horas (41%)"@es ;
    ns1:numberOfCredits 6.0 ;
    ns1:otherInformation "The computational analysis of genomic data has become an essential part of environmental and health studies. Comparative genomics, for instance, is a powerful tool to investigate what makes a species, population, or even ecosystem unique; which stands as a fundamental pillar for developing sustainability programs around OSD13-15."@es ;
    ns1:periodEndingMonth "Enero"@es ;
    ns1:periodStartingMonth "Septiembre"@es ;
    ns1:teachingPeriod "2025-26" ;
    ns1:teachingPeriodMonths "Septiembre-Enero"@es ;
    ns1:totalHours "101 horas"@es ;
    schema:activitiesWorkload "100%"@es ;
    schema:courseSchedule <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000025/2025-26/eventSchedule> ;
    schema:description "The course on Genomic Data Analysis and Visualization deals with the management, analysis and interpretation of sequencing data at genomic scale. Specifically, the course offers a practical and updated view on the most commonly used computational methods and tools in the analysis of genomes, transcripts, metagenomes and other related genomic data, covering from basic aspects such as assembly and quality control of sequences, to the comparative study of genomes, functional prediction or inference of regulatory networks. In addition, the course offers an overview of the use of such data both in the context of basic science studies (evolution, molecular biology, development) and in more applied projects (environment, clinical, genetic improvement)."@es ;
    schema:director <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/carlos.cantalapiedra%40upm.es> ;
    schema:inLanguage "Inglés"@es ;
    schema:instructor <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/carlos.cantalapiedra%40upm.es> ;
    schema:name "Análisis y Visualización de Datos Genómicos"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000025/2025-26/CE01> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CE01" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Comprender las bases moleculares y las técnicas experimentales estándares más comunes en las investigaciones ómicas (genómica, transcriptómica, proteómica, metabolómica, interactómica, etc.)/ Understanding the molecular basis and standard experimental techniques in ?omics research (genomics, transcriptomics, proteomics, interactomics, etc)."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000025/2025-26/CE04> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CE04" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Utilizar diferentes bases de datos (incluidos los bigdata), conocer sus estructuras y ontologías, aplicar la estadística a su análisis, siendo capaz de utilizar herramientas de representación y visualización/ Utilizing different databases (including those for bigdata), knowing their structures and ontologies, applying statistical analyses, and using tools for their representation and visualization."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000025/2025-26/CE08> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CE08" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Capacidad de integrar tecnologías y sistemas propios de la Inteligencia Artificial, con carácter generalista, y en contextos más amplios y multidisciplinares/ Acquire the capacity of integrating Artificial Intelligence technologies and systems in broader and multidisciplinar contexts."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000025/2025-26/CE09> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CE09" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Capacidad de interpretar los modelos de clasificación supervisada y no supervisada obtenidos al aplicar las técnicas de Aprendizaje Automático para un conjunto de datos/ Acquire the capacity of interpreting supervised and unsupervised classification methods obtained when applying Machine Learning methods to datasets."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000025/2025-26/CG01> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CG01" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Poseer los conocimientos que constituyen la base científica y tecnológica de la Biología computacional, lo que permitirá el desarrollo de ideas originales en este campo, en un contexto de investigación o desarrollo/ Having the scientific and technological knowledge in which Computational Biology is based, which will allow the development of original ideas in this field, in the context of both research or development."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000025/2025-26/CG02> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CG02" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Familiarizarse con el trabajo y los métodos de la Biología Computacional en condiciones reales, adquiriendo la capacidad de diseñar aplicaciones/experimentos de forma independiente y describir, cuantificar, analizar y evaluar críticamente los resultados obtenidos/ Becoming familiar with the work and methods in Computational Biology in real situations, acquiring the capacity of design applications/experiments in an independent manner and critically describe, quantify, analyze and evaluate the obtained results."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000025/2025-26/CG05> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CG05" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Que los estudiantes sean capaces de integrar conocimientos en el area de la Biología Computacional, de formular conclusiones, hipótesis o líneas de trabajo a partir de la información disponible, y de formarse una opinion fundamentada sobre las responsabilidades sociales y éticas vinculadas a la aplicación de sus conocimientos/ Provide students with the capacity to integrate knowledge in the area of Computational Biology, formulate conclusions, hypotheses or research lines from the available information, and with the ability to elaborate solid opinions about the social and ethic responsibilities derived from the application of their knowledge."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000025/2025-26/CT01> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CT01" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Capacidad para aplicar de forma profesional a su trabajo los conocimientos adquiridos considerando sus impactos en un contexto global y social/ Capacity to apply in their work the acquired knowledge professionally and considering the impact in a global and social context."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000025/2025-26/CT07> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CT07" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Ser capaz de manejar las tecnologías de la información y comunicación en un contexto profesional/ Be able of working with information and media technologies in a professional context."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000025/2025-26/CT08> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CT08" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Tener capacidad de análisis y síntesis para interpretar datos relevantes y abordar los problemas desde diferentes perspectivas/ To have capacity for analysis and synthesis to interpret relevant data and approach to problems from different perspectives."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000025/2025-26/RA10> a ns1:LearningResult ;
    ns1:learningResultCode "RA10" ;
    ns1:learningResultDescription "Adquirir conocimientos para el manejo de tecnologías Next Generation Sequencing (NGS) y sus aplicaciones a diferentes campos experimentales y tecnológicos"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000025/2025-26/RA11> a ns1:LearningResult ;
    ns1:learningResultCode "RA11" ;
    ns1:learningResultDescription "Adquisición de conocimientos para el ensamblaje y anotación de genomas y variantes genómicas y estudios de expresión génica diferencial"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000025/2025-26/RA12> a ns1:LearningResult ;
    ns1:learningResultCode "RA12" ;
    ns1:learningResultDescription "Aprendizaje de métodos de análisis genómico y su visualización."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000025/2025-26/didactic_resource/1> a ns1:DidacticResource ;
    ns1:bibliographyDescription "provides an understanding of the principles and approaches of functional genomics and of the potential and limitations of computational and experimental approaches to genome analysis. Free version at https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/21089240"@es ;
    ns1:bibliographyTitle "Sequence - Evolution - Function: Computational Approaches in Comparative Genomics. Koonin EV, Galperin MY. Boston: Kluwer Academic; 2003. Free online materia: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK20260/"@es ;
    ns1:bibliographyType "Bibliografía"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000025/2025-26/didactic_resource/2> a ns1:DidacticResource ;
    ns1:bibliographyDescription "Steven H. D. Haddock, Casey W. Dunn. The book shows how to use many freely available computing tools to work more powerfully and effectively. http://practicalcomputing.org/"@es ;
    ns1:bibliographyTitle "Practical Computing for Biologists"@es ;
    ns1:bibliographyType "Bibliografía"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000025/2025-26/didactic_resource/3> a ns1:DidacticResource ;
    ns1:bibliographyDescription "by Susan Holmes and Wolfgang Huber. From raw data to beautiful illuminating output, you learn to write your own scripts in the R language and to use advanced statistics packages. Online free version at https://www.huber.embl.de/msmb"@es ;
    ns1:bibliographyTitle "Modern Statistics for Modern Biology"@es ;
    ns1:bibliographyType "Bibliografía"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000025/2025-26/didactic_resource/4> a ns1:DidacticResource ;
    ns1:bibliographyDescription """Microbial Informatics and Experimentation
Beginner?s guide to comparative bacterial genome analysis using next-generation sequence data"""@es ;
    ns1:bibliographyTitle "Beginner?s guide to comparative bacterial genome analysis using next-generation sequence data"@es ;
